Experience with MS Office suite
Detail-oriented with a proficiency for researching, analyzing, and prioritizing intelligence reports and cables
Ability to work with IC tools and databases
Strong problem-solving, analytic, and written and oral communication skills
Excellent attention to detail and ability to accurately follow SOPs
Ability to work shift work/extended hours
Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to work well both independently and in a team environment
Preferred Skills and Education
BA/BS degree
Demonstrated knowledge of intelligence analysis and experience with synthesizing large amounts of data

Job Description:
Job Title:
Sr. Business Analyst - Data

Location:
US, California, Santa Clara
Role Overview:


Looking to have an impact? Come be a part of the change as we move into a new era at McAfee. Mission driven, both at the company and functional level, we share a passion for customers at the core. Critical, highly visible, senior role reporting into Director of Analytics. Analytics offers huge leverage in driving growth to the business its a great time to jump in!



Company Overview


From device to cloud, McAfee provides market-leading cybersecurity solutions for both business and consumers. We help businesses orchestrate cyber environments that are truly integrated, where protection, detection, and correction of security threats happen simultaneously. For consumers, McAfee secures your devices against viruses, malware, and other threats, both at home and away. We want to continue to shape the future of cybersecurity by working together to build best in class products and solutions.

About the role:
Act as analytics liaison between business and data engineering teams to drive results and enhanced value through improved delivery of impactful analytic insights, reports and dashboards, data visualizations, predictive models and statistical analyses.
Collaborate with stakeholders across the organization to identify, define and document standardKPIs and metrics, build and validate reports and dashboards to actively monitor and track performance.
Act as a analytics subject matter expert, developing deep understanding of data about products, consumers and business processes in our data lake and various organizational databases
Work with product development teams to provide requirements for data capture and ensure completeness and quality of data sent to the data lake
Identify data quality key issues in our dataand work with engineering and product teams to improve data quality
Responsible for end to end delivery ofreports, dashboards and data products including gathering requirements, working closely with data engineers and report developers to implement,verifying quality as well as driving user acceptance testing and adoption.
Build and present prototypes and proof of concepts on real data to ensure understanding of business use cases with tools like excel, SQL queries, tableau, MicroStrategy and Power BI
Create repeatable processes and templates for requirements documentation, technical specifications anddata quality testing etc.
About you:
Excellent business analysis andproject management skills and ability to deliver in the fast-paced evolving environment
Experience developing, implementing, testing, and maintaining methodologies for standardized and repeatable reporting for a variety of audiences
Experience working with data visualization platforms, Tableau and Microstrategy, strongly preferred
Ability to work within a climate of ambiguity
Ability to communicate effectively in a clear, logical and consistent manner, strong presentation skills
High level of attention to detail with the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, adjusting priorities as needed and meeting deadlines
Expert knowledge of SQL required
Experience with Adobe analytics preferred
Be uncompromising in pursuing data integrity and data quality improvements
Willingness and flexibility to tackle a broad range of responsibilities in a fast-paced, exciting environment
Familiarity with online data instrumentation and collection, online conversion funnel analysis
Familiarity with Data warehousing principles and methodologies like ETL, ELT, Dimensional modeling etc.
7 years of experience as Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Analyst or Data Product manager, with at least 3 years in dealing with internet or online industry data
MBA or Masters in Engineering orbusiness analytics

Experienced Hire

Additional Locations:

Healthcare Data Analyst (full-time)

Our client is looking for candidates who have solid analytical and programming skills for a job that opened up in their Performance Measurement department. This role will help promote improvements to the health insurance members overall experience. The position involves working with other departments including IT and Marketing to produce, verify and interpret data driven reports using cutting edge methods to better understand the quality of delivered health care.

This position will start as a remote (work from home) role until the companys office, located in Quincy is reopened. Training and onboarding will be conducted remotely as well.

Responsibilities Include:

- Program, execute and test clinical performance measures for HEDIS measure certification

- Work with complex health care data to develop and produce standard and ad hoc member gaps in care reports

- Identifying root causes to issues and implement coding update to resolve issues

- Ad-hoc projects as needed from the department manager or IT team

Qualifications Include:

- Bachelors Degree

- At least 1+ years of experience with healthcare data and/or related data analytic experience

- Proficiency in SQL and SAS programming

- Experience with HEDIS measurement and analysis

- Masters degree in public health, biostatistics/statistics is a plus

- Must have the ability to work individually on project and to collaborate across different departments of the organization

If you'd like to apply, please submit a resume for consideration to this posting.

We are an equal opportunity employer and consider qualified applicants for employment regardless of race, gender, gender identity, gender expression, age, color, religion, disability, veteran's status, sexual orientation, or any other protected factor.
